  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_jiaocaineedrop_jiaocai_needrop_en_453_25",
    "text": "For my father, books were knowledge. They were important to him. And yet he loved his children. What he did next was 39. Instead of punishing my brother, he sat down, took the pen from my brother's hand, and then wrote in the book himself, alongside the scribbles John had made:\" 40work, 1959, age 2.\" How many times have I looked into your beautiful face and into your warm eyes looking up at",
